40|$|The present article surveys <b>surreal</b> <b>numbers</b> with an {{informal}} approach, from their very first definition to their structure of universal real closed analytic and exponential field. Then we proceed {{to give an}} overview of the recent achievements on equipping them with a derivation, which is done by proving that <b>surreal</b> <b>numbers</b> can be seen as transseries and by finding the `simplest' structure of H-field, the abstract version of a Hardy field. All the latter notions and their context are also addressed, as well as the universality of the resulting structure for <b>surreal</b> <b>numbers.</b> Comment: 25 pages; various minor correction...|$|R
